  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "At Melbourne Airport (Tullamarine), you\u2019ll find power outlets and charging stations throughout the terminals to keep your laptop and other devices charged. Here\u2019s where you can locate them:\n\n### **Terminals 2, 3, and 4:**\n1. **Seating areas and lounges:** Many general seating areas are equipped with power outlets, often integrated into the furniture or nearby walls.\n2. **Food courts and cafes:** Outlets are commonly found near tables or counters in dining areas.\n3. **Workstations:** Designated workstations with desks and charging points are available in some areas.\n4. **Gate areas:** Check near your departure gate for charging stations or wall outlets.\n\n### **Terminal 1 (International Terminal):**\n1. **Departure lounge:** There are power outlets near seating areas and at charging stations.\n2. **Food and retail areas:** Look for outlets in cafes or dining spaces.\n3. **Workstations:** Dedicated work areas with charging points are often available.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **Lounges:** If you have access to airline lounges (e.g., Qantas Club, Virgin Australia Lounge), these often provide ample charging facilities.\n- **USB ports:** In addition to power outlets, some areas have USB ports for charging smaller devices.\n- **Portable chargers:** Consider carrying a portable charger as a backup, especially if you\u2019re in a busy area.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, ask airport staff for assistance or check the airport\u2019s website for detailed terminal maps. Safe travels!",
